    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1743317450.544979",
    "client_msg_id": "0bf514ac-adf2-48e1-a439-5474f704f8f7",
    "text": "The tacit design decisions are: (1) Hypertext is a set of pages in the same file system and (2) Lua as a dependency of the hypertext is fine. The second one is more fundamental here, because you could probably add over-the-wire links easily and compactly if your platform provides networking for you.",
