  {
    "user": "U018S42NMMM",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1743332947.767579",
    "client_msg_id": "8ca7a8e6-4596-4416-b29a-a0ea9605d91a",
    "text": "Today I added Knotend-like keyboard shortcuts to my Graph editor app: <https://codeberg.org/nilesh/grapher>\n\nBecause this editor supports compound graphs where, besides adjacency edges, nodes can also be nested using at most 1 parent per node, I needed 4 separate actions on graphs for the currently selected node:\n• Add a destination node (using the `Tab` key)\n• Add a source node (using `Shift+Tab` )\n• Add a child node (using `~`)\n• Add a parent node (using `Ctrl+~`)\nI haven't yet added keyboard shortcuts for adding \"sibling\" nodes.\n\nAlso felt sad that we don't have standardized UI components with keyboard shortcuts for manipulating trees, DAGs, plain graphs, compound graphs or hypergraphs.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1743332947.767579",
    "reply_count": 3,
    "reply_users_count": 3,
    "latest_reply": "1743338158.704799",
